quran[10]{c,v,t}:
  30,6,"The promise of Allah; Allah does not renege on His promise, but most people do not know."
  30,7,"They know only the visible worldly life; and are totally neglectful of the Hereafter."
  30,8,"Have they not inwardly pondered – that Allah has not created the heavens and the earth, and all that is between them, except with truth and a fixed term? And indeed many people deny the meeting with their Lord."
  30,9,"And did they not travel in the land to see what sort of fate befell those before them? They were stronger than them, and they cultivated the land and inhabited it more than them, and their Noble Messengers came to them with clear proofs; so it did not befit Allah’s Majesty to oppress them, but it was they who used to wrong themselves."
  30,10,"Then the fate of those who committed evil to the extreme was that they denied the signs of Allah and used to mock at them."
  30,11,"Allah initiates the creation, then will create it again – then it is to Him that you will return."
  30,12,"And on the Last Day– when it is established, the guilty* will lose all hope. (* The disbelievers.)"
  30,13,"And the partners they ascribed will not be their intercessors – and they will deny their partners."
  30,14,"And on the Last Day – that day they will all separate."
  30,15,"So those who believed and did good deeds – they will be hosted in the Garden."
